---
import type { Lang } from '../lib/locales';
import SocialLinks from './SocialLinks.astro';

interface Props {
  lang?: Lang;
}

const { lang = 'en' } = Astro.props;
const portraitUrl = 'https://github.com/anneincontext.png?size=360';
---

{lang === 'zh' ? (
  <>
    <section class="page-heading about-hero">
      <div class="about-media">
        <figure class="about-portrait" aria-label="Anne Li">
          <img
            src={portraitUrl}
            alt=""
            width="220"
            height="220"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </figure>
        <SocialLinks lang="zh" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-copy">
        <p>
          我是 Anne Li。过去十年里，我在创业公司、小团队和大型科技公司都做过前端工程师。
        </p>
        <p>
          在工程工作之外，我也一直活跃在开发者社区。我喜欢帮助开发者解决问题、补齐上下文、连接彼此，也喜欢组织技术讨论，让有用的工具、产品和想法更容易被理解。
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-profile">
      <div class="about-lede">
        <h3>我在做什么</h3>
        <p>
          我喜欢做产品、工程和社区之间的桥：Developer Experience、技术内容、开发者活动、社区运营、产品反馈循环，以及那些让开发者从“看不懂”到“愿意试一试”的上下文整理。
        </p>
        <p>
          我擅长把复杂的技术信息讲清楚，把合适的人带到同一个房间，也把一个工具、产品或生态放到更容易被理解的位置上。
        </p>
      </div>
      <ul class="about-facts" aria-label="经历亮点">
        <li><span>10+ 年</span> 自 2016 年起的工程与开发者生态经验</li>
        <li>
          <span>20+ 国家</span>
          <span class="country-flags" aria-label="走访国家与地区">🇨🇳🇸🇬🇹🇭🇮🇩🇲🇾🇻🇳🇯🇵🇳🇵🇬🇧🇪🇸🇵🇹🇫🇷🇳🇱🇩🇪🇨🇿🇦🇹🇭🇺🇮🇹🇻🇦🇬🇷🇹🇷🇦🇪</span>
          我去过 20+ 国家，将来会更多
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </>
) : (
  <>
    <section class="page-heading about-hero">
      <div class="about-media">
        <figure class="about-portrait" aria-label="Anne Li">
          <img
            src={portraitUrl}
            alt=""
            width="220"
            height="220"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </figure>
        <SocialLinks lang="en" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-copy">
        <p>
          I am Anne Li. Over the past decade, I have worked as a frontend engineer
          across startups, smaller teams, and large technology companies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Alongside my engineering work, I have stayed active in developer
          communities because I like helping developers feel less alone with hard
          problems: sharing context, connecting people, organizing technical
          conversations, and making useful tools and ideas easier to understand.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-profile">
      <div class="about-lede">
        <h3>What I Do</h3>
        <p>
          I work where product, engineering, and community meet: developer
          experience, technical content, community programs, events, product
          feedback loops, and the small connective tissue that helps developers
          feel oriented instead of lost.
        </p>
        <p>
          My strongest work tends to combine execution and translation: turning
          complex technical context into useful stories, bringing the right people
          into the same room, and making an ecosystem feel more legible from the
          outside.
        </p>
      </div>
      <ul class="about-facts" aria-label="Highlights">
        <li><span>10+ years</span> engineering and developer ecosystem experience since 2016</li>
        <li>
          <span>20+ countries</span>
          <span class="country-flags" aria-label="Countries and regions visited">🇨🇳🇸🇬🇹🇭🇮🇩🇲🇾🇻🇳🇯🇵🇳🇵🇬🇧🇪🇸🇵🇹🇫🇷🇳🇱🇩🇪🇨🇿🇦🇹🇭🇺🇮🇹🇻🇦🇬🇷🇹🇷🇦🇪</span>
          I have visited 20+ countries, with more to come
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </>
)}
